                   "message":  "SCENE-SAVE-SUBSTRATE: World -\u003e rge-scene extraction + .rge-scene save\n\nAdd the save-side inverse of the loader to rge-scene-loader (Dispatch 1\nof 2 for in-app Save). Pure substrate: no editor/binary/runtime/kernel\nchange and no new dependency.\n\n- extract_scene_from_world(world, name) -\u003e Result\u003cScene, SceneSaveError\u003e:\n  unions the four supported-component queries (Transform / Camera /\n  Light / Visibility), orders entities by ULID ascending for\n  deterministic output, and emits components in fixed order. The\n  kernel-\u003edata EntityId inverse is from_u128(id.ulid().0).\n- save_scene_world_to_path(world, path, name): .rge-scene-only writer\n  (rejects literal .rge-project and other names as UnsupportedExtension),\n  pretty RON, fs::write.\n- SceneSaveError / SceneWorldSaveError mirror the load-side taxonomy.\n- Shared TYPE_ID_* consts now used by both insert_component (decode) and\n  the extractor (encode) so the directions cannot drift.\n\nv0 fidelity (documented): entity ids + the four components only; scene\nname is caller-supplied; entity names / relations / roots emit empty;\nentities with none of the four supported components are not written.\n\n+7 headless tests (tests/scene_save_round_trip.rs): World-\u003eScene-\u003eWorld\nvalue round-trip vs the loader (spec-conformance anchor),\ndeterminism/byte-stability, empty world, component-less + unsupported-only\nskip, fidelity contract, disk save-\u003eload, unsupported-extension.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
